cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of detecting tweets that have been posted on blackmarket services to gain artificially boosted retweets. This involves natural language processing and classification tasks, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also involves regression tasks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). The problem of detecting fraudulent activity also falls under the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
